OL,3,CBail refused for Derry assault rifle
OL,4,Caccused
OL,6,FTwo Londonderry men accused of
OL,7,Fpossessing a "fully deployable" AK-47
OL,8,Fassault rifle have been refused bail.
OL,10,F59-year-old Martin Burke, of Lone Moor
OL,11,FGardens, and 56-year-old Patrick James
OL,12,FCollett, of Rossnagalliagh, are both
OL,13,Fcharged with possessing the weapon and
OL,14,Fammunition with intent to endanger
OL,15,Flife, as well as in suspicious
OL,16,Fcircumstances.
OL,18,FThe pair appeared at the city's
OL,19,Fmagistrates court on Friday morning.
