OL,6,FDuring the hearing a PSNI detective
OL,7,Fsaid Mr Collett had been observed
OL,8,Fleaving Mr Burke's home carrying a
OL,9,Fdark bag and placing it in the boot of
OL,10,Fhis car.
OL,12,FThe officer said the vehicle was
OL,13,Fstopped by police a short time later
OL,14,Fwhen the "fully functional and fully
OL,15,Fdeployable" weapon was discovered.
OL,17,FObjecting to bail, a prosecution
OL,18,Flawyer told the court that the
OL,19,F"sinister aspect" of this case was
OL,20,Fthat the weapon and ammunition found
OL,21,Fwere compatible.
