OL,6,FShe also told the court inference
OL,7,Fcould be drawn that the items were
OL,8,Fbeing moved on behalf of the New IRA.
OL,10,FA defence lawyer for Mr Collett said
OL,11,Fhis client had felt pressured to move
OL,12,Fthe items, telling the court Mr
OL,13,FCollett could be described as a
OL,14,F"patsy".
OL,16,FHe said there was no prospect of Mr
OL,17,FCollett using the weapon, saying the
OL,18,Faccused had no involvement with any
OL,19,Fillegal organisations.
