OL,6,FMr Burke's defence described him as a
OL,7,F"chronic alcoholic" who spends his day
OL,8,Fin the pub.
OL,10,FThe lawyer told the court Mr Burke's
OL,11,Ffamily believe he is a vulnerable man
OL,12,Fwho had been "exploited".
OL,14,FResponding the bail application, the
OL,15,Fjudge said too many questions remain
OL,16,Fover the case, which he acknowledged
OL,17,Fis at an early stage.
OL,19,FBail was refused for both defendants
OL,20,Fwho will appear in court again next
OL,21,Fmonth.
